    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "4071fe62_0440147c",
        "filename": "android/android-emu/android/virtualscene/Renderer.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 318,
      "author": {
        "id": 1082465
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-12-07T16:50:47Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Looks like from here that scene objects are 1:1 with all of their instances, so if we go with an explicit unload function for scene objects, it will also remove their instances.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 315,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 318,
        "endChar": 78
      },
      "revId": "83baa21ec8b9018beb1eb30d5316a7e987647c54",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "1cedffae_fb5b416d",
        "filename": "android/android-emu/android/virtualscene/Renderer.h",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 181,
      "author": {
        "id": 1082465
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-12-07T16:50:47Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Something might be up here in regards to ownership/lifetime of materials and meshes.\n\nIn the CL, it\u0027s all shared_ptrs with the apparent meaning being that once we delete all instances of a particular material or mesh, the underlying GL resource also gets freed.\n\nBut, it looks like to create the GL resources, it\u0027s based on an explicit call in Renderer, or in Effect.\n\nI\u0027m also not a big fan of shared_ptr for its implicit behavior. shared_ptr also introduces lots of synchronization and since it\u0027s working in pointers, is not cache friendly.\n\nFor something simpler to start with, since we\u0027re currently just dealing with the one scene OBJ, can we make them non shared_ptr and have an explicit function to unload materials and meshes? Perhaps we can have a method to explicitly unload a SceneObject or Effect if they are currently 1:1 with resources; that way, when the user wants to load a different scene for AR, we just explicitly unload the current set of SceneObjects and load a different set.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 181,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 181,
        "endChar": 19
      },
